caption: Tom Yum Koong is the first restaurant we tried when we moved to the neighborhood and is so good it became our instant go-to. Everyone is SO nice, they do their own local delivery and are very fast, and the food is always delicious. The menu has something for everyone and portion sizes are impressive. Spend your money here!
Great Thai place, looking forward to my next meal!
easy pickup, everything packaged neatly and securely for transport. food is reliably delicious and ready when promised
Tom Yum Koong soup is delicious if u like some spice.  Maybe my favorite soup I've ever had.

This is my go-to Thai Grubhub order restaurant. Delivery is unbeatably fast, always arrives freshly made and hot. Sometimes the flavor of the sauces are not exactly spot on but the staple noodle dishes and appetizers area consistently tasty. Definitely recommend!
Food portion was very small for the prices. Food was not good either.
The food is constantly fresh and flavorful, cashiers hands over excellent customer service. I really like how neat it is and character. Highly recommended.
They make living in Medford Square a less odious affair.  A reliable go-to for great Thai.  An extremely nice establishment
The food is EXCELLENT and very fresh. Delivery  is very quick and the staff are very polite
Was hesitant about basil fried rice due to reviews and it was amazing😭 spicy and loaded with basil, tofu, and veggies. Highly recommend!
The drunken noodles are excellent

last night was the first time in this restaurant. But It is definitely not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the good service, with the great  food and booze and with the decent pay. We will definitely come back in a short time.
The food is consistently fresh and delicious, employees provides fantastic service. I really like how clean it is and atmosphere. Would recommend to others.
Foods average but very over priced! Definitely better restaurants around
Great food!

Nice staff with overall good food.  1)  Boat Noodle Soup - $14.95 – thai rice noodle soup in meat broth with pork, beansproat, garnish with scallions, cilantro, and fried garlic. Delicious noodles. Soup had a nice kick to it. Perfect for a cold day and fills the stomach without being too heavy.  2)  Jungle Beef - $13.95 – grilled thai style beef with sticky rice. Beef was a bit tough but well flavored. Sticky rice was warm and not stale. Overall, decent & filling without being greasy or heavy but wouldn’t get it again.  3)  Dessert = Fried Bananas - $5.95 – friend bananas in spring rolls with a nice douse of honey. Not too sweet, freshly made, and warm.
Service is wounderful food is great ! Very polite & attentive .
1st time going here. Tiny little place but great tasting food. Very busy

Unfortunately, they have jacked up their price exponentially. For instancs the phuket fried rice use to have shrimp, mussels, and scallops and now they have itemized all the seafood items as separate items.
Off the beaten path. The plates weren't standard dishes but tasty. Dishes were a decent price and the Thai iced teas were tasty!
Best drunken noodles I’ve ever had and this is my favorite Thai dish! Spicy and the basil flavor is not overpowering like many drunken noodle dishes can be at other restaurants! Highly recommended!!!

Wasn't my choice wast bad I got cashew  chicken problem  is I have had cashew chicken at cheesecake factory....cheesecake factory  makes cashew chicken so amazing anything  else seems ehhh waste of a cheat meal
Nice spot for Thai. The spicy ginger sauce is fire!
Boat noodle soup!
Pretty decent place. I would recommend the golden sacks.

The worst! I ordered food for $65 dollars. It never arrived. When I  saw that the ordered did not arrive I called and at first phone was always off the hook. When they finally answered they told me first the food had left and 1 and a half prior. When I asked for the driver's number they told me they could not locate it and they would call me back. They never did. WHen I called back, the woman on the phone kept asking me for the address ( I live around the corner) and when I complained she hung up on me! Do not bother with this place.
I should give this place a no star. That's how bad it was.  Our first time there and definitely the last. I ordered Chicken Pad Thai and it tasted like grease and oil, I couldn't even eat it.
Delicious!  Super friendly as well.
Authentic Thai food! Very delicious and impressive ! And the service is very good. I like this restaurant.
Great Thai food, whether it's sit-down or delivery!!
Best mango curry I have ever had in my life. Delicious, couldn’t recommend more!
Not worth the trip! Ordered the drunken noodles with shrimp, and it was garbage. Wasted $13.38 had 2 bites, never again. Avoid this place at all costs can't give half a star or I would.
Love this place and their drunken noodle
Love this place, best Thai place around hands down! Always order red curry with tofu... it’s literally the best. Fast service and delicious food. Everything we’ve ordered has been great!
I am obsessed with this Thai food, specifically the crispy chicken basil. Every time I am away for a bit, the first thing I have when I get back to Medford is this dish.
Excellent
They didn’t add any duck sauce to my order.
Amazing!!!! Food is soooo good
I always get delivery and it arrives hot and quickly! Soups are delicious, drunken noodle, currys etc are always perfect and the delivery men are so courteous.
Good food and prices. Clean.
I love this place! Food is always fresh - the thai rolls and chicken fried rice is amazing. Always great service. Highly recommend!
Good foods with good service!
Any time restaurant with a grandma is worth a stop. This place has limited parking and it's worth the parking ticket. #parked at usps
Food was very good, very friendly.  Not crowded, but seems like lots of  takeout .

Ordered Red Curry, Tom Yung Koong, and Tofu Triangles for takeout. The food was really greasy and had a lot of artificial tasting flavors. The tofu was saturated with so much oil, I could not eat it. The Tom Yung Koong had some kind of sickly sweet syrup drizzled into it- like eating melted candy. The Red Curry was okay but had a strange almost perfume-y, floral taste to it that masked all of the curry flavor.  Easy to order and came on time, but simply can't recommend due to the quality of the food. Sad to say my search for great Thai takeout in Boston/Cambridge continues.
Absolutely love this place. Amazing food. Great service. I always order the same stuff via delivery and they automatically know it’s me. And deliver the food within 40min. Hands down the best!!
Good soup
Wonderful place, wonderful people.  Amazing food.  You won't find better massaman curry anywhere!  Believe me, I've tried.
Very

Yummy, yummy Thai food.  I always get the same thing which is the mango curry with seafood.  I ususlly get sticky or briwn rice.  It has great Tom Yum soup, hince the name. It doesnt have the best pad thai but the curry dishes and soup more than make up for it.   It's a small restaurant so advanced planning is needed for groups, but my toddlers and I pop in for lunch every now and then and they always accomodate.  It's also conveniently located on Forest Street near Route 60 / Salem / High St.  Great service.  Reasonably priced.  They deliver!  It's really the only Thai option in Medford, so it has a lot going for it.  You just have to have reasonable expectations for a restaurant of it's size.
It's OK.  The pad see you was good, pineapple fried rice was just ok.

ZERO STARS!!!!!!!!!  The combo plate was ABSOLUTELY TERRIBLE!!!!! Everything was frozen, processed food.  The chicken and beef satay was NOT SATAY!!!!  It was VERY DRY, overcooked, looked, smelled, and tasted funny and HIGHLY questionable if was real meat.  The ENTIRE plate was thrown in the TRASH!!!  The MOST HORRIBLE restaurant experience EVER!!!!!!!!  Please REMOVE "THAI" from your description.  VERY VERY VERY VERY VERY VERY FALSE ADVERTISEMENT!!!!!  WASTE of money and WASTE of restaurant space!!!!!  Sell to real chefs who will serve customers authentic food, not food from freezer to fryer.  ABSOLUTELY DISGUSTING FOOD HERE AND WILL NEVER PATRONIZE HERE EVER!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Spicy crispy tofu is excellent!
I’ve only ever gotten delivery but it’s always been great. The best, most flavorful Thai in the area. If you’re out for deliciousness, I highly recommend it.
Best asian fusion food in Medford!!

Simple restaurant. The food was Ok not more, medium size portions. At the end with the bill, came 18% gratitude. I don't know for what. Not fancy, the fork and knife were wraped by a cheep paper napkin. We did not have any special requests. Restaurant was almost empty. We were 6 people  4 of which were children. Maybe this is the way to get more out of tourists.

Would give a 4.5 stars if I could! This is a great Thai place for quick takeout or a sit-down meal. The food is super flavorful, which is a must for Thai cuisine. I especially recommend the drunken noodles with chicken. (Not pictured here -- the picture shows the garlic udon noodles, which are also a fan favorite.) The owner is the smiliest man you'll ever meet. Jokes aside, the management is awesome. Definitely recommend to anyone in the Medford Square area!

Small but delightful restaurant with very friendly staff and a quick service. It is perhaps not a place for a glam dinner but if you need to grab a lunch or dinner and want some good food, I would certainly recommend this place.
Place is clean and tidy good for a small group.noodles and soups are ok. Would not suggest if you have an Indian palate and not willing to experiment..
food is delicious but only street parking
Excellent food and good value. Not a place for much ambiance, but for me food, value, and service are 1,2, and 3 and service was also good. Better than most Thai food I had while in Thailand. Yum!
Great service and tasty food. Awesome restaurant in Medford area.
Owners were very responsive and highly personalized the service and experience. Get the fish curry! Fried bananas were also excellent as a dessert.
Honestly best food I have ever eaten. Service is incredible as well
Delicious food and drinks. Entrees made with seasonal, local veggies and meats.Friendly staff.
Fast and delicious food at a reasonable price. What more could you ask for. Be warned, their "Spicy" level is REALLY spicy and I can usually handle my heat.
The ambiance may be lacking but the food is excellent. Rich and flavorful curry with well cooked fresh veggies. Great Thai!

Friendly staff and very high quality food. I highly recommend getting the Tofu triangles with peanut sauce. The Padthai is also very good and the seafood is fresh. LASTLY, Plead don't forget to order the Sweet sticky rice with mango for dessert because it's out of this world.

Delicious good. Very clean. Really nice owner. Cannot believe my first time. Soup chicken noodleveith rice noodles was superb. I have never seen so many take out dinners for delivery. Thought it might be new years.

Great food.

Went there for dinner based on a recommendation. Lovely, fast service and laid-back atmosphere. Tried a couple of starters and we had two of their house curries; - both were very well cooked and plated for an overall authentic Thai food experience. Also very good value for money as we ended up taking half of the portions home! Would recommend.
Great food.  Never had a bad dish.  Pineapple fried rice, cashew chicken, pad thai, ... all very tasty.  Great Satay and Singha beer to wash down.

This is the go-to Thai place in Medford for my boyfriend and I. He loves the Pad Thai and I love the Delight of Three. It's can be a little more expensive than other Thai places depending on what you order, but the quality of the food is great and I usually make two or even three meals out of it.
They food is good but they take a little longer to serve the food

Nothing was horrible but nothing tasted like any other Thai food I've ever had. Everything tasted a little weird and I can't quite explain it, but I will not be going back there.
Great local Thai joint
Love the food here!
Nice and very taste food
I only do take out and the menu is adequate. Good Pad Thai and satay.
I live next door and order from there 2 times a week. Owner and start are really nice and good is really good.
Food was excellent. Presentation of three delight dish was lovely.  Staff was great.

Great food, though our order took longer than expected to be ready (we were told 25 minutes and it took 40 min). It was a rainy Friday, so they may have been busier than usual. The meats are all well marinated and the basil dishes have a nice spicy kick to it. The scallion pancake was very flavorful as well
The superior duck is very crispy. My go-to take-out and dine in place
I had an amazing spicy seafood soup and delicious pad thai! Great food and service!

A fantastic Local Gem of Thai Food for Medford. Wonderful flavor and presentation!

Great little Thai place. Clean and quiet. The food is excellent, and the service was top-notch. They also serve beer and wine.  We started with their Crab Rangoon (my favorite in the Boston area so far, wasn't greasy) and then we had bowls of their Tom Yum Koong soup - a spicy coconut concoction. Lastly we shared an entree of the Basil Crispy chicken w/vegetables​. The presentation was beautiful and the meal was phenomenal!  Try this place out if you're craving Thai, it won't hurt wallet.
Excellent Thai food!
Good food + Reliable friendly service = Great Business
Nice staff. Seating always available
Very friendly service and the pad Thai is very delicious here.
This is by far the best Thai joint in Medford. Mostly take out, but the staff is excellent if you decide to dine in.
Food is great! Decent prices. Good customer service, very friendly staff.
Food arrived cold and there was no indication that the yum nua salad would be loaded with cilantro. Spice level was nice and hot. Past orders have been better, so I'd say this place is hit and miss.
Awesome service, great food, and just wooow!!!!!

The ingredients were fresh, but the taste wasn't amazing.
Nice place for Thai food
Our favorite place for Thai food.
Quaint, friendly service, attention to detail, fair price. Enjoy folks
Basil Fried Rice...incredible. Love this place.

I've been ordering from them for over a year now and have yet to be disappointed.  Their delivery guys are always smiling, and are prompt and polite.  The curries are fantastic and while I could go for spicier, they certainly make you sweat the way a good curry is supposed to.  Taro pancakes are solid, and the fried rice dishes are not overly sweet or oily.  Having spent a few years in Southern China, I was impressed with that last bit, as coming home, fried rice dishes have a tendency to be horribly over-oiled/seasoned. I can't speak to how authentic it is, but I and the few friends that have dined with me have all raved about it.
Friendly staffs, good taste!

I wish I could rate this place 10 stars. I've been ordering from here for about 5 years now, mostly delivery with the ocasional visit in restaurant. Their curries are out of this world. Papaya salad is the best I've had in all of Boston, and I've dined more than my fair share in Thai restaurants. Anytime we have guests, we order from this place, they never fail to produce exceptional food, and our guests are always amazed. I even had a guest who grew up in Thailand try this place; she has been living in New York City for over 10 years so I was nervous about what she would think about the food... she said it was some of the best Thai she has ever had. Period. Some few of our favorites: Panang, Massaman and Green curries, we prefer them on the spicier side; Papaya salad; Fried Basil Tofu; Drunken noodles.

I wish I could rate this 0 stars. They are AWFUL. I placed an order online and they tried to deliver it 5 hours early. Then when it came time for the order to come when it was supposed to, they were over half an hour late. Customer service is awful, and they didn't even try to make it right. Don't waste your time here. You'll be extremely disappointed.
find the food lack flavors, could be better.

There aren't many Thai options in Medford (that I have found) so this place is pretty solid for Thai food in the area.  The food tastes flavorful and is fairly authentic.  They don't mix too much on the menu or make it too much about the fusion asian side of the house.  Most of their dishes can be made vegetarian if you ask but i've pretty much stuck to the Pad Thai with Tofu or the Pad See Yew with Tofu and I haven't been disappointed.  Their spring rolls are also good but nothing that exciting.
Excellent food, very polite and courteous service. Reasonably priced, especially for lunch items.

Not too good, bad some would say.. Pad Thai and drunken noodle were like two giant masses of flavorless noodles.  Basil rice had a hint of spice but barely any chicken.  Order someplace else, most def not 4 stars like yelp would have you believe..
